Tom Dooley... ##

21
00:02:50,099 --> 00:02:51,532
Somebody will see.

22
00:02:51,601 --> 00:02:53,034
Come with me.

23
00:02:59,242 --> 00:03:02,177
Does Mary Ann kiss as good as I do?

24
00:03:02,245 --> 00:03:03,610
How would I know?

25
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,772
Oh, you!

26
00:03:16,693 --> 00:03:18,627
You said we were special.

27
00:03:18,695 --> 00:03:20,788
I meant everything.

28
00:03:45,154 --> 00:03:48,590
Ohh.

29
00:03:48,658 --> 00:03:50,091
Oh, Gary.

30
00:04:11,180 --> 00:04:12,272
No.

31
00:04:12,348 --> 00:04:13,440
Gary.

32
00:04:13,516 --> 00:04:14,608
Come on.

33
00:04:14,684 --> 00:04:16,117
No.

34
00:04:16,185 --> 00:04:17,618
Come on.

35
00:04:17,687 --> 00:04:19,552
Oh.

36
00:04:23,893 --> 00:04:26,259
Somebody's there.

37
00:04:36,205 --> 00:04:37,638
We weren't doing anything.

38
00:04:37,707 --> 00:04:39,140
We were just mess-

39
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:40,641
Aah!

40
00:04:50,954 --> 00:04:52,182
Please stop.

41
00:04:58,027 --> 00:04:59,119
Stop.

42
00:05:01,230 --> 00:05:04,097
No!

43
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:05,259
Help!

44
00:05:05,335 --> 00:05:07,929
Aah!

45
00:07:20,571 --> 00:07:21,663
Hi, girl.

46
00:07:21,738 --> 00:07:23,171
Excuse me.
Hi, boy.

47
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,673
Hey, you speak English?

48
00:07:24,741 --> 00:07:27,676
How far is it
to Camp Crystal Lake?

49
00:07:28,912 --> 00:07:30,345
That far, huh?

50
00:07:30,414 --> 00:07:32,348
Okey-dokey.
See you later.

51
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:33,508
Ugh!

52
00:07:41,692 --> 00:07:45,128
It's 7:01 on Friday the 13th of June.

53
00:07:45,195 --> 00:07:46,628
This is Big Dave.

54
00:07:46,697 --> 00:07:51,134
It's time for you lazy bones
to get out of bed.

55
00:07:51,201 --> 00:07:54,136
It's black cat day
in Crystal Lake.

56
00:08:01,178 --> 00:08:04,045
I must've cleaned
that tow jack 82 times.

57
00:08:04,114 --> 00:08:07,015
Excuse me. How far
is Camp Crystal Lake?

58
00:08:07,084 --> 00:08:08,016
# Your heart... ##

59
00:08:13,423 --> 00:08:15,084
What is it, Enos?

60
00:08:15,158 --> 00:08:17,251
About 20 miles?

61
00:08:17,327 --> 00:08:18,419
About that.

62
00:08:18,495 --> 00:08:19,587
Camp Blood.

63
00:08:19,663 --> 00:08:21,324
They're opening that place again?

64
00:08:21,398 --> 00:08:22,831
Lots of luck.

65
00:08:22,899 --> 00:08:25,663
Can I get a bus or something?

66
00:08:25,736 --> 00:08:26,828
Not likely.

67
00:08:26,903 --> 00:08:30,066
You going down
to the crossroads, Enos?

68
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:32,574
What about a lift?
That'll be halfway.

69
00:08:32,643 --> 00:08:34,076
No sweat, Trudy.

70
00:08:34,144 --> 00:08:35,907
O.K., kid, let's move it.

71
00:08:35,979 --> 00:08:37,071
Name's Annie.

72
00:08:37,147 --> 00:08:39,775
All right, Annie.
Let's go.

73
00:08:46,690 --> 00:08:48,624
All the girls up there

74
00:08:48,692 --> 00:08:51,126
going to look as good as you?

75
00:08:51,194 --> 00:08:52,525
I don't know.

76
00:08:52,596 --> 00:08:55,030
You're going to Camp Blood,
ain't ya?

77
00:08:55,098 --> 00:08:58,033
Goddamn it, Ralph, get out of here.

78
00:08:58,101 --> 00:08:59,534
Get.
Leave people alone!

79
00:08:59,603 --> 00:09:00,934
You'll never come back again.

80
00:09:01,004 --> 00:09:03,165
Oh, shut up, Ralph.

81
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:06,300
It's got a death curse!

82
00:09:09,146 --> 00:09:12,411
He's a real prophet of doom,
ain't he?

83
00:09:12,482 --> 00:09:14,347
Climb up, miss.

84
00:09:32,736 --> 00:09:34,169
I tell you,

85
00:09:34,237 --> 00:09:37,172
he's causing problems enough
for your boss

86
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,208
with all that talk.

87
00:09:39,276 --> 00:09:41,210
Goddamn nuisance.

88
00:10:05,702 --> 00:10:07,727
He tell you anything?

89
00:10:07,804 --> 00:10:08,896
Who?

90
00:10:08,972 --> 00:10:10,064
Your boss...

91
00:10:10,140 --> 00:10:11,232
Steve Christy.

92
00:10:11,308 --> 00:10:15,642
I'll be cooking
for 50 kids and 10 staff.

93
00:10:15,712 --> 00:10:19,148
The campers will mostly be,
like, inner city children.

94
00:10:19,216 --> 00:10:22,185
No, I mean about what happened.

95
00:10:24,221 --> 00:10:25,279
No.

96
00:10:30,727 --> 00:10:31,819
Come on.

97
00:10:31,895 --> 00:10:34,329
There's something
you're not telling me.

98
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:37,325
Quit.

99
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,867
Quit now.

100
00:10:38,935 --> 00:10:41,961
Quit?
Why would I want to quit?

101
00:10:42,038 --> 00:10:45,269
Camp Crystal Lake is jinxed.

102
00:10:45,342 --> 00:10:46,434
Oh, terrific.

103
00:10:46,510 --> 00:10:47,943
Not you, too?

104
00:10:48,011 --> 00:10:51,469
You sound like your
crazy friend back there- Ralph.

105
00:10:51,548 --> 00:10:52,981
Maybe.
Did Christy tell you

106
00:10:53,049 --> 00:10:54,983
about two kids murdered in '58?

107
00:10:55,051 --> 00:10:58,214
Boy drowning in '57?

108
00:10:58,288 --> 00:10:59,721
Bunch of fires.

109
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:02,725
Nobody knows who did any of them.

110
00:11:02,793 --> 00:11:05,660
In 1962 they was going to open up.

111
00:11:05,729 --> 00:11:07,162
The water was bad.

112
00:11:07,230 --> 00:11:09,664
Christy will wind up
like his folks-

113
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:11,223
crazy and broke.

114
00:11:11,301 --> 00:11:14,737
He's been up there a year
fixing up that place.

115
00:11:14,805 --> 00:11:16,238
He must've dropped $25,000.

116
00:11:16,306 --> 00:11:17,739
And for what?

117
00:11:17,808 --> 00:11:19,332
Ask anybody.

118
00:11:20,577 --> 00:11:22,238
Quit.

119
00:11:22,312 --> 00:11:24,644
I can't.

120
00:11:24,714 --> 00:11:25,806
Dumb kids.

121
00:11:25,882 --> 00:11:27,315
Know-it-alls.

122
00:11:27,384 --> 00:11:29,648
Just like my nieces.

123
00:11:29,719 --> 00:11:32,210
Heads full of rocks.

124
00:11:32,289 --> 00:11:34,723
You're an American original.

125
00:11:34,791 --> 00:11:36,725
I'm an American original.

126
00:11:38,128 --> 00:11:39,527
Dumb kid.

127
00:11:39,596 --> 00:11:42,895
At least I'm not afraid of ghosts.

128
00:12:03,687 --> 00:12:05,245
Take care of yourself, kid.

129
00:12:05,322 --> 00:12:08,223
No sweat.
Thanks a lot for the lift.

130
00:12:40,223 --> 00:12:41,656
Hey, uh, Marcie.

131
00:12:41,725 --> 00:12:42,919
What?

132
00:12:42,993 --> 00:12:45,860
You really think there'll be
other gorgeous women

133
00:12:45,929 --> 00:12:47,863
at Camp Crystal Lake
besides yourself?

134
00:12:47,931 --> 00:12:50,365
Sex all you ever think about?

135
00:12:50,433 --> 00:12:51,866
No, no.
Absolutely not.

136
00:12:51,935 --> 00:12:53,163
Ha!

137
00:12:53,236 --> 00:12:56,171
Sometimes I just think
about kissing women.

138
00:12:57,974 --> 00:12:59,407
Ahh!

139
00:12:59,476 --> 00:13:00,670
Oh!

140
00:13:00,744 --> 00:13:01,836
Ahh.

141
00:13:05,515 --> 00:13:06,607
Ahh!

142
00:13:57,233 --> 00:14:00,669
Hey, want to give me
a hand over here?

143
00:14:00,737 --> 00:14:03,099
Sure.

144
00:14:03,173 --> 00:14:04,265
Alice!

145
00:14:04,341 --> 00:14:07,139
I want to get
this tree stump out.

146
00:14:07,210 --> 00:14:10,111
Get on this side.
On three, O.K.? Alice!

147
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:11,112
Coming.

148
00:14:14,184 --> 00:14:17,312
That's great. That's great.
I'm Steve Christy.

149
00:14:17,387 --> 00:14:18,319
Jack Burrel.

150
00:14:18,388 --> 00:14:19,821
Marcie Cunningham,
Ned Rubinstein.

151
00:14:19,889 --> 00:14:21,322
Welcome to Camp Crystal Lake.

152
00:14:21,391 --> 00:14:22,551
This is Alice.

153
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:24,559
Hi. Steve,
cabin B's all ready.

154
00:14:24,627 --> 00:14:26,561
Is Bill finished
cleaning the boathouse?

155
00:14:26,629 --> 00:14:29,723
I haven't seen him
for half an hour.

156
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:31,733
I want him to start painting.

157
00:14:31,801 --> 00:14:33,234
What about Brenda?

158
00:14:33,303 --> 00:14:35,737
You told her to set up archery.

159
00:14:35,805 --> 00:14:37,238
I'd rather she paint.

160
00:14:37,307 --> 00:14:39,241
I thought we had two weeks.

161
00:14:39,309 --> 00:14:42,244
I'll show you where
you can get changed.

162
00:14:42,312 --> 00:14:44,246
You have your clothes with you?

163
00:14:44,314 --> 00:14:45,781
Back here.

164
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:53,655
Here. Let me give you
a hand with that.

165
00:14:53,723 --> 00:14:54,815
Thank you.

166
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:05,600
You got it?

167
00:15:05,668 --> 00:15:06,760
Mm-hmm.

168
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:28,623
You draw very well.

169
00:15:30,026 --> 00:15:33,962
Thanks. I wish I had
more time to do it.

170
00:15:35,198 --> 00:15:36,290
Aah.

171
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:39,301
When did you do this?

172
00:15:39,369 --> 00:15:40,461
Last night.

173
00:15:41,704 --> 00:15:44,138
Do I really look like that?

174
00:15:44,207 --> 00:15:46,198
You did last night.

175
00:15:51,214 --> 00:15:53,239
You're very talented.

176
00:15:55,718 --> 00:15:57,379
And very pretty.

177
00:15:58,721 --> 00:15:59,813
Thank you.

178
00:15:59,889 --> 00:16:03,985
This really isn't
your cup of tea, is it?

179
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:05,493
Any particular reason?

180
00:16:05,562 --> 00:16:07,655
It's just a problem I have.

181
00:16:07,730 --> 00:16:09,698
It's nothing personal.

182
00:16:12,669 --> 00:16:14,102
You want to leave?

183
00:16:14,170 --> 00:16:16,434
I may have to go
back to California

184
00:16:16,506 --> 00:16:17,700
to straighten something out.

185
00:16:22,679 --> 00:16:23,771
Come on.

186
00:16:23,847 --> 00:16:25,781
Give me another chance.

187
00:16:25,849 --> 00:16:27,282
Stay a week.

188
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:30,114
Help get the place ready.

189
00:16:30,186 --> 00:16:32,620
By Friday, if you're not happy,

190
00:16:32,689 --> 00:16:35,681
I'll put you on the bus myself.

191
00:16:35,758 --> 00:16:37,191
All right. Friday.

192
00:16:37,260 --> 00:16:39,956
I'll give it a week.

193
00:16:47,203 --> 00:16:48,602
Thanks, Alice.

194
00:17:03,153 --> 00:17:06,589
Bill, Steve wants to know
if we need more paint.

195
00:17:06,656 --> 00:17:09,819
The paint's all right.
We'll need more thinner.

196
00:17:09,893 --> 00:17:11,326
O.K. I'll tell him.

197
00:17:11,394 --> 00:17:12,827
The others show up?

198
00:17:12,896 --> 00:17:14,329
Yeah, everybody except that girl

199
00:17:14,397 --> 00:17:16,228
who's supposed to handle
the kitchen- Annie.

200
00:17:16,299 --> 00:17:17,732
Think you'll last all summer?

201
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:20,735
I don't know if I'll last all week.

202
00:17:20,803 --> 00:17:22,737
I'll tell Steve about the thinner.

203
00:17:22,805 --> 00:17:24,067
Fine.

204
00:17:39,055 --> 00:17:40,989
Do you want it listed separately?

205
00:17:41,057 --> 00:17:42,149
That's right.

206
00:17:42,225 --> 00:17:44,659
After lunch, Brenda,
finish the archery range.

207
00:17:44,727 --> 00:17:46,160
If Annie gets here,

208
00:17:46,229 --> 00:17:48,163
get her started in the kitchen.

209
00:17:48,231 --> 00:17:49,664
Do your best, all right?

210
00:17:49,732 --> 00:17:51,666
I'll be back sometime after lunch.

211
00:17:51,734 --> 00:17:53,167
Supposed to rain like hell.

212
00:17:53,236 --> 00:17:55,170
Get as much done as possible.

213
00:17:55,238 --> 00:17:57,672
I don't want to get too far behind.

214
00:17:57,740 --> 00:17:58,832
See you.

215
00:17:58,908 --> 00:18:00,000
Bye-bye.

216
00:18:01,711 --> 00:18:03,576
He neglected to mention
that downtown

217
00:18:03,646 --> 00:18:06,080
they call this place Camp Blood.

218
00:18:06,149 --> 00:18:09,778
Next you'll say there are
poisonous snakes in the outhouse

219
00:18:09,852 --> 00:18:11,581
and crocodiles in the lake.

220
00:18:11,654 --> 00:18:14,782
No, the crocodiles
are in the cabins.

221
00:18:40,183 --> 00:18:41,480
Ta-da!

222
00:18:43,753 --> 00:18:45,186
Are you crazy?

223
00:18:45,255 --> 00:18:47,689
Want to see my trick shot?

224
00:18:47,757 --> 00:18:49,782
It's even better.

225
00:18:49,859 --> 00:18:53,763
I don't believe you!

226
00:18:56,699 --> 00:18:59,133
You know, you're beautiful
when you're angry, sweetheart.

227
00:18:59,201 --> 00:19:00,293
Yeah?

228
00:19:00,369 --> 00:19:04,237
Did you come to help me
or scare me to death?

229
00:19:04,306 --> 00:19:07,241
Do that again,
I'll tack you on the wall.

230
00:19:07,309 --> 00:19:08,936
I love that sexy talk!

231
00:19:33,502 --> 00:19:34,730
Hi.

232
00:19:34,804 --> 00:19:37,238
I'm going to Camp Crystal Lake.

233
00:19:51,187 --> 00:19:54,714
I guess I always wanted
to work with children.

234
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:57,224
I hate when people call them kids.

235
00:19:57,293 --> 00:19:58,726
Sounds like little goats.

236
00:19:58,794 --> 00:20:02,730
But when you've had a dream
as long as I have,

237
00:20:02,798 --> 00:20:04,231
you'll do anything.

238
00:20:24,220 --> 00:20:27,951
Wasn't that the road
for Camp Crystal Lake back there?

239
00:20:33,229 --> 00:20:35,663
Uh, I think we better stop.

240
00:20:39,235 --> 00:20:40,702
Please?

241
00:20:42,738 --> 00:20:45,172
Stop, please?

242
00:20:45,241 --> 00:20:50,205
Please, stop!

243
00:20:56,252 --> 00:20:57,344
Oh!

244
00:21:05,861 --> 00:21:07,886
Ow.

245
00:21:07,963 --> 00:21:09,055
Ow!

246
00:21:13,602 --> 00:21:14,694
Ow.

247
00:22:13,462 --> 00:22:16,156
No.

248
00:22:19,134 --> 00:22:20,123
No.

249
00:22:39,088 --> 00:22:40,521
Little to the left.

250
00:22:40,589 --> 00:22:42,022
No, no, no, no.

251
00:22:42,091 --> 00:22:43,319
O.K., baby, slow it down.

252
00:22:43,392 --> 00:22:45,053
Let's go.

253
00:22:45,127 --> 00:22:47,823
O.K. Good, good, good.

254
00:23:02,277 --> 00:23:05,212
If you were a flavor of ice cream,

255
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,645
what would it be?

256
00:23:06,715 --> 00:23:07,807
Rocky Road.

257
00:23:07,883 --> 00:23:09,441
Hey!

258
00:23:23,298 --> 00:23:26,233
What's that vitamin "C" stuff
do for you anyway?

259
00:23:26,301 --> 00:23:29,828
Vitamin C's supposed to neutralize
the nitrates or something.

260
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:32,864
What's the matter?

261
00:23:32,941 --> 00:23:34,374
Do you see something?

262
00:23:37,579 --> 00:23:39,444
No, nothing.

263
00:23:42,184 --> 00:23:43,276
Oh!

264
00:23:43,352 --> 00:23:44,683
Ned!

265
00:23:45,921 --> 00:23:47,013
Get out of here!

266
00:23:47,089 --> 00:23:48,181
Ned!

267
00:23:48,257 --> 00:23:49,349
Aah!

268
00:23:49,425 --> 00:23:51,359
I'm getting to you.

269
00:23:51,427 --> 00:23:52,519
Very slowly.

270
00:23:52,594 --> 00:23:54,323
Ha ha! You!

271
00:23:54,396 --> 00:23:55,829
Hey, you guys.

272
00:23:55,898 --> 00:23:58,833
You ready to go back to work?

273
00:23:58,901 --> 00:24:00,368
Yeah.

274
00:24:00,436 --> 00:24:01,528
Ohh.

275
00:24:01,603 --> 00:24:02,797
Come on, Alice.

276
00:24:02,871 --> 00:24:04,133
Help!

277
00:24:04,206 --> 00:24:07,300
Help! Help!

278
00:24:07,376 --> 00:24:08,638
Something's wrong with Ned.

279
00:24:09,812 --> 00:24:11,871
Get a life preserver!

280
00:24:29,064 --> 00:24:30,497
Is it far?
Can he swim?

281
00:24:30,566 --> 00:24:33,194
He's right around here somewhere.

282
00:24:34,536 --> 00:24:36,470
Go ahead.
Dive for him.

283
00:24:38,841 --> 00:24:40,274
There he is.

284
00:24:40,342 --> 00:24:41,775
Come on, you guys.
Help us.

285
00:24:41,844 --> 00:24:43,277
Watch his head.

286
00:24:43,345 --> 00:24:44,778
Here.
Grab hold of that.

287
00:24:44,847 --> 00:24:45,939
O.K.

288
00:24:46,014 --> 00:24:47,447
Move it away.

289
00:24:47,516 --> 00:24:49,609
Watch his head.

290
00:24:49,685 --> 00:24:50,777
Got him?

291
00:24:50,853 --> 00:24:51,945
Yeah.

292
00:24:57,860 --> 00:25:00,294
Do you give mouth-to-mouth?

293
00:25:00,362 --> 00:25:02,296
Yeah.
Pull up his head.

294
00:25:06,301 --> 00:25:07,393
Oh, God.

295
00:25:07,469 --> 00:25:08,936
Come on, Neddie.

296
00:25:09,004 --> 00:25:09,902
Come on.

297
00:25:09,972 --> 00:25:11,234
Oh, Neddie!

298
00:25:11,306 --> 00:25:13,103
Oh, Jesus Christ!

299
00:25:49,244 --> 00:25:50,336
Aah!

300
00:25:55,851 --> 00:25:58,779
Bill!

301
00:25:58,854 --> 00:26:00,287
Come here quick!

302
00:26:00,355 --> 00:26:01,515
Hurry!

303
00:26:05,827 --> 00:26:07,192
What is it?

304
00:26:07,262 --> 00:26:09,730
There's a snake over there.

305
00:26:09,798 --> 00:26:10,890
Where?

306
00:26:18,307 --> 00:26:19,740
What do I do?

307
00:26:19,808 --> 00:26:20,900
Kill it.

308
00:26:20,976 --> 00:26:22,409
It might bite.

309
00:26:22,477 --> 00:26:24,911
Haven't you ever been in the woods?

310
00:26:24,980 --> 00:26:26,413
We're not in the woods.

311
00:26:26,481 --> 00:26:28,415
Jesus, Bill, what are you doing?

312
00:26:28,483 --> 00:26:29,916
There's a snake in here.

313
00:26:29,985 --> 00:26:31,919
Then why are we in here?

314
00:26:31,987 --> 00:26:33,420
Feet, don't fail me now.

315
00:26:33,488 --> 00:26:34,853
There it is!
Ahh!

316
00:26:34,923 --> 00:26:37,858
I can't sleep with a snake in here.

317
00:26:37,926 --> 00:26:39,860
Nobody told us anything
about snakes.

318
00:26:39,928 --> 00:26:41,020
Kill it.

319
00:26:41,096 --> 00:26:42,529
You heard the lady.

320
00:26:42,598 --> 00:26:45,533
I can't get it till it comes out.

321
00:26:45,601 --> 00:26:46,533
Call him.

322
00:26:46,602 --> 00:26:48,536
How do you call a snake?

323
00:26:48,604 --> 00:26:50,037
I'll flush it out!

324
00:26:50,105 --> 00:26:51,470
No!

325
00:26:51,540 --> 00:26:52,837
- Aah!
- Aah!

326
00:26:55,043 --> 00:26:56,476
I got it!

327
00:26:56,545 --> 00:26:57,637
Where?

328
00:26:57,713 --> 00:27:00,045
I got it!

329
00:27:00,115 --> 00:27:01,639
Kill it!

330
00:27:09,625 --> 00:27:11,058
Is it dead?

331
00:27:11,126 --> 00:27:14,562
Either that or it's got
a very short clone.

332
00:27:14,630 --> 00:27:16,222
Oh, God.

333
00:27:16,298 --> 00:27:19,734
Well, at least we know
what's for dinner.

334
00:27:19,801 --> 00:27:21,860
- Oh! - Oh,
Marcie! - Gross!

335
00:27:25,774 --> 00:27:27,207
I make good salad.

336
00:27:27,276 --> 00:27:29,210
Want me to make bread pudding?

337
00:27:29,278 --> 00:27:30,404
Great.
We've got hamburger.

338
00:27:30,479 --> 00:27:31,912
None for me, thank you.

339
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:34,915
There are apples.
Know how to make apple pie?

340
00:27:34,983 --> 00:27:36,416
Oh, sure.
No sweat.

341
00:27:36,485 --> 00:27:38,419
Oh, what is going on?

342
00:27:48,664 --> 00:27:49,892
Oh, shit.

343
00:27:51,933 --> 00:27:54,367
All right, who are you people?

344
00:27:54,436 --> 00:27:55,528
Camp counselors.

345
00:27:55,604 --> 00:27:57,037
Neddie's just fooling around.

346
00:27:57,105 --> 00:27:58,538
Right, I'm just-

347
00:27:58,607 --> 00:28:00,040
Can it, Cochise.

348
00:28:00,108 --> 00:28:01,541
Steve Christy hire you people?

349
00:28:01,610 --> 00:28:03,043
He pay you for this?

350
00:28:03,111 --> 00:28:04,203
Nice bike.

351
00:28:04,279 --> 00:28:05,712
See if you're smoking, boy.

352
00:28:05,781 --> 00:28:07,146
Don't smoke.
Causes cancer.

353
00:28:07,215 --> 00:28:09,149
You just get off a spaceship?

354
00:28:09,217 --> 00:28:12,152
Colombian gold, man, grass,
hash, the weed. Dig it?

355
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,653
Hey, what's he talking about?

356
00:28:13,722 --> 00:28:15,155
Hey, don't get smart.

357
00:28:15,223 --> 00:28:17,157
Me? I'm dumb as they come.

358
00:28:17,225 --> 00:28:20,126
Not another word
out of you, understand?

359
00:28:20,195 --> 00:28:21,628
Really.
Nothing's going on here.

360
00:28:21,697 --> 00:28:23,631
We're getting the place in shape.

361
00:28:23,699 --> 00:28:25,132
In shape for what?

362
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:26,724
Officer, can we help?

363
00:28:26,802 --> 00:28:28,235
Looking for somebody.

364
00:28:28,303 --> 00:28:29,395
Who's that?

365
00:28:29,471 --> 00:28:31,905
A guy named Ralph.
Town crazy.

366
00:28:31,973 --> 00:28:33,406
No crazy people around here.

367
00:28:33,475 --> 00:28:36,410
I told you to sit on it, Tonto.

368
00:28:36,478 --> 00:28:40,414
I got word that Ralph
was pedaling out this way

369
00:28:40,482 --> 00:28:42,006
spouting his gospel.

370
00:28:42,084 --> 00:28:44,018
We haven't seen anybody here,
Officer.

371
00:28:44,086 --> 00:28:45,178
Just us.

372
00:28:45,253 --> 00:28:46,982
This Ralph, is he dangerous?

373
00:28:47,055 --> 00:28:48,989
Every time that loony gets drunk,

374
00:28:49,057 --> 00:28:50,490
he gets his calling.

375
00:28:50,559 --> 00:28:52,993
I spend the morning in court,

376
00:28:53,061 --> 00:28:54,995
he gets a week in jail.

377
00:28:55,063 --> 00:28:56,496
Cycle Two, where are you?

378
00:28:56,565 --> 00:28:57,862
Come in, Cycle Two.

379
00:28:57,933 --> 00:29:00,367
This is Dorf at Camp Crystal Lake.
Over.

380
00:29:00,435 --> 00:29:01,868
Haul it back in.

381
00:29:01,937 --> 00:29:04,872
Chief wants you back on the double.

382
00:29:04,940 --> 00:29:08,103
Roger that. 10-4.
On my way. Out.

383
00:29:09,778 --> 00:29:12,144
Never keep the chief waiting.

384
00:29:14,783 --> 00:29:17,217
You kids keep your noses clean.
Understand?

385
00:29:17,285 --> 00:29:19,913
You'll be hearing
from me if you don't.

386
00:29:22,791 --> 00:29:26,818
We ain't going to stand
for no weirdness out here.

387
00:30:08,069 --> 00:30:09,161
Aah!

388
00:30:10,739 --> 00:30:13,264
I'm the messenger of God.

389
00:30:13,341 --> 00:30:17,471
You're doomed if you stay here.

390
00:30:19,648 --> 00:30:21,081
This place is cursed.

391
00:30:21,149 --> 00:30:23,310
Cursed.

392
00:30:24,853 --> 00:30:26,787
It's got a death curse.

393
00:30:26,855 --> 00:30:28,288
Who are you?

394
00:30:28,356 --> 00:30:29,789
What do you want?

395
00:30:29,858 --> 00:30:31,792
God sent me.

396
00:30:31,860 --> 00:30:33,794
Get out of here, man.

397
00:30:33,862 --> 00:30:35,796
I got to warn you.

398
00:30:35,864 --> 00:30:39,027
You're doomed if you stay.

399
00:30:40,368 --> 00:30:42,563
Go.

400
00:30:42,637 --> 00:30:44,002
Go!

401
00:30:55,016 --> 00:30:57,450
I think we just met Ralph.

402
00:30:57,519 --> 00:30:59,487
God, what's next?

403
00:31:10,164 --> 00:31:11,756
You're doomed.

404
00:31:11,832 --> 00:31:14,266
You're all doomed.

405
00:31:40,094 --> 00:31:41,527
Who likes them rare?

406
00:31:41,595 --> 00:31:42,687
Me.

407
00:31:42,763 --> 00:31:45,197
How can you guys eat that stuff?

408
00:31:45,266 --> 00:31:46,699
It looks like dead animals.

409
00:31:46,767 --> 00:31:48,667
Dead animals?
That's the old counselors.

410
00:31:48,736 --> 00:31:49,930
You cannibal.

411
00:31:50,004 --> 00:31:52,871
If you'd mix right,
you'd get all your protein.

412
00:31:52,940 --> 00:31:54,874
Too bad Annie never showed up.

413
00:31:54,942 --> 00:31:57,376
She was supposed to be a good cook.

414
00:31:57,445 --> 00:31:59,276
Don't expect me to replace her.

415
00:31:59,346 --> 00:32:00,438
Trouble?

416
00:32:00,514 --> 00:32:02,448
Bad bulb or no power.

417
00:32:02,516 --> 00:32:04,950
It seems a little gloomy in here.

418
00:32:05,019 --> 00:32:07,886
Steve taught me how to use
the emergency generator.

419
00:32:07,955 --> 00:32:09,889
Town power lines are real lousy.

420
00:32:09,957 --> 00:32:12,892
Don't you love that macho talk?

421
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:15,087
The emergency generator.

422
00:32:15,162 --> 00:32:16,254
Let's go.

423
00:32:16,330 --> 00:32:18,264
I'll take care of these.

424
00:32:18,332 --> 00:32:20,266
Will you watch the burgers?

425
00:32:20,334 --> 00:32:21,426
Burn them.

426
00:32:21,502 --> 00:32:22,594
Want cheese?

427
00:32:22,670 --> 00:32:23,796
Yeah, uh-huh.

428
00:32:23,871 --> 00:32:26,806
You really think
you can get this to work?

429
00:32:26,874 --> 00:32:28,307
I don't know.

430
00:32:28,375 --> 00:32:30,309
Hey, this looks like the one

431
00:32:30,377 --> 00:32:32,811
at my uncle's cabin in Maine.

432
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:34,313
Well, here goes.

433
00:32:34,381 --> 00:32:35,814
What an antique.

434
00:32:35,883 --> 00:32:36,975
O.K.

435
00:32:44,859 --> 00:32:47,293
What hath God wrought?

436
00:34:04,939 --> 00:34:06,133
Hello?

437
00:34:15,816 --> 00:34:17,579
Can I help you?

438
00:34:24,658 --> 00:34:25,750
Hello?

439
00:34:26,827 --> 00:34:28,055
Hello?

440
00:34:29,496 --> 00:34:30,588
Come on.

441
00:34:30,664 --> 00:34:32,097
I'm coming.
I'm coming.

442
00:34:33,834 --> 00:34:34,926
Man.

443
00:34:35,002 --> 00:34:36,435
Ooh, wind's come up.

444
00:34:36,503 --> 00:34:38,937
It shifted a good 180 degrees.

445
00:34:39,006 --> 00:34:43,170
Need someone to hold on to.

446
00:34:46,680 --> 00:34:48,113
What about Ned?

447
00:34:48,182 --> 00:34:49,615
I don't love Ned.

448
00:34:49,683 --> 00:34:52,618
He keeps acting like such a jerk.

449
00:34:52,686 --> 00:34:53,778
Neddie!

450
00:34:53,854 --> 00:34:55,287
Don't call him.

451
00:34:55,356 --> 00:34:57,790
I thought you wanted to give him

452
00:34:57,858 --> 00:34:59,792
one of your motherly lectures.

453
00:34:59,860 --> 00:35:02,795
Neddie's going to do
whatever Neddie wants to.

454
00:35:02,863 --> 00:35:04,797
Ooh, it's going to storm.

455
00:35:04,865 --> 00:35:08,733
It'll tear down that valley
like a son of a gun.

456
00:35:08,802 --> 00:35:11,566
I've feared storms
since I was little.

457
00:35:11,639 --> 00:35:12,799
No. Really?

458
00:35:12,873 --> 00:35:16,741
Yeah. I've had this dream
about five or six times

459
00:35:16,810 --> 00:35:18,744
where I'm in a thunderstorm-

460
00:35:18,812 --> 00:35:19,904
Mm-hmm.

461
00:35:19,980 --> 00:35:21,948
and it's raining really hard.

462
00:35:22,016 --> 00:35:25,452
It sounds like pebbles
when it hits the ground.

463
00:35:25,519 --> 00:35:26,952
I can hear it.

464
00:35:27,021 --> 00:35:30,957
I try to block out
the sound with my hands,

465
00:35:31,025 --> 00:35:32,458
only it doesn't work.

466
00:35:32,526 --> 00:35:35,757
It just keeps getting
louder and louder.

467
00:35:35,829 --> 00:35:37,126
And then...

468
00:35:38,332 --> 00:35:40,766
the rain turns to blood.

469
00:35:41,902 --> 00:35:45,804
The blood washes away
in little rivers.

470
00:35:47,341 --> 00:35:50,242
Then the sound stops.

471
00:35:52,846 --> 00:35:54,279
It's just a dream.

472
00:35:54,348 --> 00:35:55,781
Yeah, I know.

473
00:35:55,849 --> 00:35:58,283
I call it my shower dream.

474
00:35:58,352 --> 00:36:00,786
Hey, hey, this is no dream.

475
00:36:00,854 --> 00:36:03,880
Come on.
We're going to get soaked.

476
00:38:03,010 --> 00:38:05,877
Jack and Marcie are
going to get drenched.

477
00:38:05,946 --> 00:38:08,972
Not if they're where
I think they are.

478
00:38:35,142 --> 00:38:36,234
That's nice.

479
00:38:36,310 --> 00:38:37,402
Mm-hmm.

480
00:38:37,478 --> 00:38:38,570
Hey...

481
00:38:38,645 --> 00:38:40,579
I know what we can do.

482
00:38:40,647 --> 00:38:42,080
We're going to play Monopoly.

483
00:38:39,649 --> 00:38:41,082
I hate Monopoly.

484
00:38:41,150 --> 00:38:43,175
Not the way I play it.

485
00:38:43,252 --> 00:38:46,483
We're going to play strip Monopoly.

486
00:38:46,556 --> 00:38:48,490
You have got to be kidding.

487
00:38:48,558 --> 00:38:50,492
What about if Steve walks in?

488
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:51,993
We'll give him a handicap.

489
00:38:52,061 --> 00:38:53,995
He can keep his boots on.

490
00:38:54,063 --> 00:38:55,496
Everything else goes.

491
00:38:55,565 --> 00:38:56,998
Instead of paying rent,

492
00:38:57,066 --> 00:38:58,499
you pay clothes.

493
00:38:58,568 --> 00:39:00,001
Bill can be banker,

494
00:39:00,069 --> 00:39:01,866
unless, of course, he's chicken.

495
00:39:01,938 --> 00:39:05,305
Heaven help you if you land
on one of my hotels.

496
00:39:05,375 --> 00:39:07,502
See if Marcie left any grass.

497
00:39:07,577 --> 00:39:09,511
What happened to my 500?

498
00:39:09,579 --> 00:39:12,707
Right there.
Where's my shoe?

499
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:23,685
I'm not going to pass go
without a glow.

500
00:40:23,753 --> 00:40:25,687
We already rolled for you.

501
00:40:25,755 --> 00:40:27,188
You're going last.

502
00:40:27,256 --> 00:40:28,689
Oh, and Community Chest

503
00:40:28,758 --> 00:40:31,192
cannot give you your clothes back.

504
00:40:32,361 --> 00:40:33,453
Double sixes.

505
00:40:33,529 --> 00:40:34,962
I get to roll again.

506
00:40:35,031 --> 00:40:36,965
I think we're being hustled.

507
00:40:37,033 --> 00:40:39,024
I think you're right.

508
00:40:42,371 --> 00:40:45,306
You are so fine.

509
00:40:52,381 --> 00:40:54,315
Where you going?

510
00:40:54,383 --> 00:40:56,647
I got to pee.

511
00:41:01,390 --> 00:41:03,756
Hurry back, O.K.?

512
00:41:03,826 --> 00:41:05,760
It's getting cold in here.

513
00:41:14,837 --> 00:41:16,771
Save my place for me.

514
00:41:16,839 --> 00:41:17,931
Oh, yeah.

515
00:41:36,526 --> 00:41:37,618
Five.

516
00:41:37,693 --> 00:41:40,628
1, 2, 3, 4, 5.
"Baltic Avenue. "

517
00:41:40,696 --> 00:41:42,129
I'll buy it.

518
00:41:42,198 --> 00:41:44,632
No one ever lands
on Baltic Avenue.

519
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:46,133
It's a pretty color.

520
00:41:46,202 --> 00:41:47,294
O.K.

521
00:41:47,370 --> 00:41:48,803
Come on.

522
00:41:48,871 --> 00:41:49,963
Ha! Eight!

523
00:41:50,039 --> 00:41:52,974
1, 2, doo doo doo
doo doo doo.

524
00:41:53,042 --> 00:41:55,306
Baltic Avenue.

525
00:41:55,378 --> 00:41:57,312
You owe me one boot.

526
00:41:57,380 --> 00:41:58,472
Coming.

527
00:41:58,548 --> 00:41:59,981
Alice draws first blood.

528
00:42:00,049 --> 00:42:03,416
That's a terrible way
to talk about my feet.

529
00:42:03,486 --> 00:42:04,578
Thank you.

530
00:42:04,654 --> 00:42:05,746
Who's next?

531
00:42:07,323 --> 00:42:09,757
You know, I think I'm beginning

532
00:42:09,825 --> 00:42:11,258
to like this game.

533
00:42:11,327 --> 00:42:14,763
Just wait until he lands on
my old Kentucky home.

534
00:42:14,830 --> 00:42:16,263
More beer?
More beer.

535
00:42:16,332 --> 00:42:18,502
Let's see... the railroad.

536
00:44:14,818 --> 00:44:17,753
"40 Yards To The Outhouse,
by Willie Makeit. "

537
00:44:17,821 --> 00:44:20,255
Come on, kids.

538
00:44:20,323 --> 00:44:22,757
You can do better than that.

539
00:44:24,327 --> 00:44:25,851
Jack?

540
00:44:31,334 --> 00:44:33,097
# Jack? ##

541
00:44:37,173 --> 00:44:38,470
Jack?

542
00:44:48,351 --> 00:44:49,784
When I looked into that mirror,

543
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:52,117
I knew I'd always be ugly.

544
00:44:53,356 --> 00:44:58,225
I said, "Lizzie,
you'll always be plain. "

545
00:45:01,364 --> 00:45:03,161
Hello?

546
00:45:24,487 --> 00:45:25,579
Aha!

547
00:45:41,337 --> 00:45:42,429
Ned?

548
00:45:45,842 --> 00:45:48,106
Hey, come on, you guys.

549
00:46:14,304 --> 00:46:15,794
Allee allee in free!

550
00:46:32,989 --> 00:46:35,048
Must be my imagination.

551
00:46:39,362 --> 00:46:40,294
Aah!

552
00:46:52,342 --> 00:46:54,207
Hello.

553
00:46:54,277 --> 00:46:57,212
Worst run of bad luck
since Richard Nixon.

554
00:46:57,280 --> 00:46:59,271
You can always call it quits.

555
00:46:59,349 --> 00:47:02,284
Fat chance.
You're two steps from Pacific Avenue

556
00:47:02,352 --> 00:47:03,717
and Skin City.

557
00:47:09,793 --> 00:47:11,727
Well, what can I say?

558
00:47:11,795 --> 00:47:14,730
It's not much, but I call it home.

559
00:47:15,799 --> 00:47:16,731
Aah!

560
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:17,732
Oh, no!

561
00:47:17,801 --> 00:47:19,234
I'll get it.

562
00:47:19,302 --> 00:47:20,735
Get the money!

563
00:47:20,804 --> 00:47:22,101
Oh, God!

564
00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:23,605
It's crazy out there.

565
00:47:23,673 --> 00:47:26,608
I think I left
my cabin windows open.

566
00:47:26,676 --> 00:47:27,734
Shoot.

567
00:47:29,312 --> 00:47:33,248
Well, we'll have to finish
this game some other night.

568
00:47:33,316 --> 00:47:36,547
Just when it was
getting interesting.

569
00:47:36,619 --> 00:47:38,917
See you guys in the morning.

570
00:47:38,988 --> 00:47:40,250
See ya.

571
00:47:40,323 --> 00:47:42,757
Night.

572
00:47:42,826 --> 00:47:44,350
Ohh!

573
00:47:51,234 --> 00:47:52,758
Look at this mess.

574
00:47:52,836 --> 00:47:55,771
Were you really going
to go ahead with this?

575
00:47:55,839 --> 00:47:58,273
Actually, I hadn't made up my mind.

576
00:47:58,341 --> 00:48:01,469
We'll have to finish
the game another night.

577
00:48:18,294 --> 00:48:21,229
Steve, is there
anything else you want?

578
00:48:21,297 --> 00:48:23,731
No, no, thanks, Sandy.
I'm fine.

579
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:26,735
You can't go back out in that rain.

580
00:48:26,803 --> 00:48:28,236
You wanna get drowned?

581
00:48:28,304 --> 00:48:29,271
I've got to.

582
00:48:29,339 --> 00:48:31,739
I've got six
new counselors at camp.

583
00:48:31,808 --> 00:48:34,242
They are babes in the woods.

584
00:48:34,310 --> 00:48:39,247
They'll be O.K. if they don't
have to come out in the rain.

585
00:48:39,315 --> 00:48:41,249
What do I owe you?

586
00:48:41,317 --> 00:48:43,751
Just a night on the town, Steve.

587
00:48:43,820 --> 00:48:45,754
You know what I mean.

588
00:48:45,822 --> 00:48:48,757
That's O.K.
2.25 and that's it.

589
00:48:51,828 --> 00:48:52,886
Thank you.

590
00:49:06,276 --> 00:49:07,709
Here's your change, Steve.

591
00:49:07,777 --> 00:49:09,210
You keep it, Sandy.

592
00:49:09,279 --> 00:49:10,712
Thank you.

593
00:49:10,780 --> 00:49:11,712
Drive careful.

594
00:49:11,781 --> 00:49:12,713
I will.

595
00:49:12,782 --> 00:49:13,771
Good night.

596
00:52:39,355 --> 00:52:40,287
Hi.

597
00:52:40,356 --> 00:52:41,584
Hi, Steve.

598
00:52:41,657 --> 00:52:43,784
That's supposed to go
through anything.

599
00:52:43,860 --> 00:52:45,293
Not dragging a trailer.

600
00:52:45,361 --> 00:52:47,295
Can you give me a lift?

601
00:52:47,363 --> 00:52:50,298
A counselor will bring me back
in the morning.

602
00:54:11,314 --> 00:54:13,748
Help me!

603
00:54:38,341 --> 00:54:40,275
Help me!

604
00:55:08,304 --> 00:55:09,737
Hello!

605
00:55:13,309 --> 00:55:14,742
Hello!

606
00:55:14,810 --> 00:55:16,243
Over here!

607
00:55:16,312 --> 00:55:17,244
Please!

608
00:55:17,313 --> 00:55:19,372
Somebody help me!

609
00:55:19,448 --> 00:55:20,380
Hello!

610
00:55:23,819 --> 00:55:25,252
Hello!

611
00:55:29,325 --> 00:55:30,758
Hello!

612
00:55:36,332 --> 00:55:37,264
Hello?

613
00:55:43,339 --> 00:55:44,772
Come quickly!

614
00:55:44,840 --> 00:55:45,772
Please!

615
00:55:45,841 --> 00:55:47,775
Come quickly!
Help!

616
00:56:02,358 --> 00:56:03,723
Where are you?

617
00:56:03,793 --> 00:56:05,226
Hello!

618
00:56:25,314 --> 00:56:27,248
Hello!

619
00:56:33,823 --> 00:56:34,983
All right!

620
00:56:37,126 --> 00:56:40,061
Come on out!
It's not funny anymore!

621
00:56:41,831 --> 00:56:43,765
It's not funny at all.

622
00:56:55,778 --> 00:56:59,915
Aah!

623
00:57:48,496 --> 00:57:50,487
Bill.

624
00:57:51,566 --> 00:57:52,897
Hi.

625
00:57:52,968 --> 00:57:53,900
Generator's O.K.

626
00:57:53,969 --> 00:57:56,062
I thought I heard a scream.

627
00:57:56,137 --> 00:57:58,071
I didn't hear anything
through that wind.

628
00:57:58,139 --> 00:57:59,572
It sounded like Brenda.

629
00:57:59,641 --> 00:58:01,404
I better take a look.

630
00:58:01,476 --> 00:58:05,344
And somebody turned on
the lights at the archery range.

631
00:58:07,415 --> 00:58:09,349
I can't see anything.

632
00:58:09,417 --> 00:58:11,851
They're off now.

633
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:14,855
I'm going to check it out.

634
00:58:14,923 --> 00:58:16,356
Bill?

635
00:58:16,424 --> 00:58:18,358
Can I come?

636
00:58:18,426 --> 00:58:19,859
Come on then.

637
00:58:22,897 --> 00:58:27,367
Brenda!

638
00:58:32,440 --> 00:58:33,873
Where is she?

639
00:58:35,443 --> 00:58:38,378
She must be with Jack and Marcie.

640
00:58:41,449 --> 00:58:42,381
Alice?

641
00:58:42,450 --> 00:58:43,382
Yeah?

642
00:59:04,406 --> 00:59:07,341
What is going on?

643
00:59:11,413 --> 00:59:12,345
Come on!

644
00:59:19,821 --> 00:59:20,753
Jack!

645
00:59:20,822 --> 00:59:22,756
Jack, open the door!

646
00:59:25,326 --> 00:59:26,759
Where are they?

647
00:59:26,828 --> 00:59:28,762
I don't know.

648
00:59:28,830 --> 00:59:29,762
Come on.

649
00:59:34,936 --> 00:59:36,767
Brenda.

650
00:59:36,838 --> 00:59:38,271
Marcie?

651
00:59:39,841 --> 00:59:40,773
Hey, guys.

652
00:59:40,842 --> 00:59:42,275
Jack.

653
00:59:42,343 --> 00:59:43,776
Neddie?

654
00:59:48,850 --> 00:59:51,785
Bill, I think
we should call someone.

655
00:59:51,853 --> 00:59:55,289
If this is a joke,
I'm gonna brain 'em.

656
00:59:55,356 --> 00:59:56,288
I'm serious.

657
00:59:56,357 --> 00:59:59,292
I really think
we should call someone.

658
01:00:08,369 --> 01:00:09,301
Sucker's locked.

659
01:00:09,370 --> 01:00:10,803
Where's the key?

660
01:00:10,872 --> 01:00:12,305
I don't know.

661
01:00:12,373 --> 01:00:13,806
Wait a minute.

662
01:00:22,817 --> 01:00:24,250
Watch out.

663
01:00:29,324 --> 01:00:30,256
Careful.

664
01:00:32,827 --> 01:00:34,761
Let me get the light.

665
01:00:42,837 --> 01:00:44,270
What's wrong?

666
01:00:44,339 --> 01:00:45,271
It's dead.

667
01:00:45,340 --> 01:00:46,773
Try the pay phone.

668
01:00:46,841 --> 01:00:49,776
Do you have a dime or a quarter?

669
01:01:00,855 --> 01:01:01,787
Hello?

670
01:01:01,856 --> 01:01:05,121
Oh, this damn thing's dead, too.

671
01:01:20,308 --> 01:01:22,242
What's the matter with it?

672
01:01:22,310 --> 01:01:23,743
It's wet.

673
01:01:23,811 --> 01:01:25,244
I don't know.

674
01:01:25,313 --> 01:01:28,749
Why don't we just
hike out of here right now?

675
01:01:28,816 --> 01:01:31,751
It's 10 miles
to the nearest crossroads.

676
01:01:31,819 --> 01:01:33,252
Steve will be back soon.

677
01:01:33,321 --> 01:01:35,255
We can use his Jeep.

678
01:01:35,323 --> 01:01:38,759
Don't worry. Probably some
stupid explanation for all this.

679
01:01:38,826 --> 01:01:39,758
Like what?

680
01:01:39,827 --> 01:01:42,261
We'll be laughing
about this tomorrow.

681
01:01:42,330 --> 01:01:43,262
I promise.

682
01:01:46,834 --> 01:01:49,428
Let's get out of this rain.

683
01:01:52,340 --> 01:01:55,776
It's not bad enough
to have Friday the 13th,

684
01:01:55,843 --> 01:01:58,175
but to have a full moon, too.

685
01:01:58,246 --> 01:02:00,271
We keep statistics.

686
01:02:00,348 --> 01:02:03,283
We have more accidents, more rapes,

687
01:02:03,351 --> 01:02:05,285
more robberies, more homicides,

688
01:02:05,353 --> 01:02:07,787
more of everything
with a full moon.

689
01:02:07,855 --> 01:02:09,288
It upsets people.

690
01:02:09,357 --> 01:02:11,257
Makes 'em nuts.

691
01:02:11,326 --> 01:02:14,420
You're making science
out of coincidence.

692
01:02:14,495 --> 01:02:18,295
Hear ol' Ralph
was out your way today.

693
01:02:18,366 --> 01:02:22,234
His wife was a nervous wreck
till we got him home.

694
01:02:22,303 --> 01:02:25,739
That's all I need-
crazy Ralph running around.

695
01:02:25,807 --> 01:02:28,105
Well, the rain's stopping.

696
01:02:28,176 --> 01:02:31,111
It was a pisser while it lasted.

697
01:02:31,179 --> 01:02:32,612
Sergeant Tierney, come in.

698
01:02:32,680 --> 01:02:34,739
Sergeant Tierney, car niner.

699
01:02:34,816 --> 01:02:36,750
This is Tierney.

700
01:02:36,818 --> 01:02:39,252
Rescue squad with jaws of life.

701
01:02:39,320 --> 01:02:40,753
Near mile marker 17.

702
01:02:40,822 --> 01:02:41,754
Possible fatal.

703
01:02:41,823 --> 01:02:43,757
Three, maybe more trapped.

704
01:02:43,825 --> 01:02:44,757
Head-on.

705
01:02:44,826 --> 01:02:46,760
Roger.
Acknowledge receipt.

706
01:02:46,828 --> 01:02:49,422
Estimate arrival 15 minutes.

707
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:00,774
Let you off here, Steve.

708
01:03:00,842 --> 01:03:01,774
Sure.

709
01:03:03,344 --> 01:03:04,777
Thanks.

710
01:03:04,846 --> 01:03:05,778
Good luck.

711
01:03:44,218 --> 01:03:45,150
Hello?

712
01:03:45,219 --> 01:03:47,050
Who is that?

713
01:03:50,858 --> 01:03:51,790
Oh, hi.

714
01:03:51,859 --> 01:03:54,794
What are you doing
out in this mess?

715
01:05:15,843 --> 01:05:18,277
What do you think happened?

716
01:05:18,346 --> 01:05:19,711
I don't know.

717
01:05:21,783 --> 01:05:24,217
Generator's probably out of gas.

718
01:05:24,285 --> 01:05:25,718
I'll go check it.

719
01:05:27,288 --> 01:05:30,223
Do you want me to come with you?

720
01:05:30,291 --> 01:05:31,815
Why don't you stay here

721
01:05:31,893 --> 01:05:34,726
and try and get some sleep.

722
01:05:34,796 --> 01:05:36,696
I'll be right back.

723
01:07:07,822 --> 01:07:08,754
Gas.

724
01:07:44,458 --> 01:07:45,720
Bill!

725
01:07:45,793 --> 01:07:47,226
Bill?

726
01:07:53,801 --> 01:07:55,234
Generator.

727
01:09:56,724 --> 01:09:58,783
Bill!

728
01:10:01,362 --> 01:10:02,795
Bill!

729
01:10:04,365 --> 01:10:05,798
Bill!

730
01:10:08,869 --> 01:10:09,801
Bill!

731
01:10:11,372 --> 01:10:12,304
Bill?

732
01:10:16,877 --> 01:10:17,809
Bill.

733
01:10:19,313 --> 01:10:20,245
Bill?

734
01:10:32,827 --> 01:10:33,759
Bill?

735
01:10:37,832 --> 01:10:39,265
Bill!

736
01:10:45,339 --> 01:10:47,364
Aah!

737
01:10:48,843 --> 01:10:49,832
Bill!

738
01:10:53,848 --> 01:10:54,780
Aah!

739
01:10:56,350 --> 01:10:57,783
Oh, my God!

740
01:10:59,353 --> 01:11:00,285
Aah!

741
01:14:02,836 --> 01:14:04,770
What am I gonna do?

742
01:14:10,343 --> 01:14:12,277
Brenda!

743
01:14:32,799 --> 01:14:33,731
God!

744
01:14:46,813 --> 01:14:48,747
Oh, my God.

745
01:15:17,844 --> 01:15:19,709
Steve! Oh, Steve!

746
01:15:23,316 --> 01:15:24,715
Who are you?

747
01:15:24,784 --> 01:15:26,718
Well, I'm Mrs. Voorhees,

748
01:15:26,786 --> 01:15:29,084
an old friend of the Christies.

749
01:15:29,155 --> 01:15:31,214
Oh, thank God you're here.

750
01:15:31,291 --> 01:15:33,919
It's been such a nightmare!

751
01:15:33,993 --> 01:15:37,224
I can't help you
if you don't calm down.

752
01:15:37,297 --> 01:15:39,231
She's dead and he's dead...

753
01:15:39,299 --> 01:15:41,233
Oh, my God, poor Bill!

754
01:15:41,301 --> 01:15:44,236
All right.
Come on, dear, then show me.

755
01:15:44,304 --> 01:15:45,236
No.

756
01:15:45,305 --> 01:15:46,738
But it's all right.

757
01:15:46,806 --> 01:15:48,239
I'll take care of you.

758
01:15:48,308 --> 01:15:50,742
I used to work for the Christies.

759
01:15:50,810 --> 01:15:52,243
What's going on here?

760
01:15:52,312 --> 01:15:55,247
It's just this place and the storm.

761
01:15:55,315 --> 01:15:56,748
That's why you're upset.

762
01:15:56,816 --> 01:15:58,249
No! They're all dead!

763
01:15:58,318 --> 01:15:59,751
They're all dead!

764
01:15:59,819 --> 01:16:01,753
All right.
I'll go look.

765
01:16:01,821 --> 01:16:03,254
Please don't leave me.

766
01:16:03,323 --> 01:16:05,257
They'll kill you, too.

767
01:16:05,325 --> 01:16:07,316
I'm not afraid.

768
01:16:24,978 --> 01:16:27,208
Oh, my Lord.

769
01:16:29,515 --> 01:16:31,210
So young.

770
01:16:31,284 --> 01:16:33,616
So pretty.

771
01:16:33,686 --> 01:16:36,655
What monster could've done this?

772
01:16:38,124 --> 01:16:40,922
Bill's out there.

773
01:16:40,994 --> 01:16:43,724
Oh, God.
This place!

774
01:16:43,796 --> 01:16:47,232
Steve should never have
opened this place again.

775
01:16:47,300 --> 01:16:49,734
There's been too much trouble here.

776
01:16:49,802 --> 01:16:53,238
Did you know that
a young boy drowned

777
01:16:53,306 --> 01:16:56,241
the year before those
two others were killed?

778
01:16:56,309 --> 01:16:58,743
The counselors weren't
paying any attention.

779
01:16:58,811 --> 01:17:03,145
They were making love while
that young boy drowned.

780
01:17:03,216 --> 01:17:05,241
His name was Jason.

781
01:17:07,353 --> 01:17:10,288
I was working
the day that it happened,

782
01:17:10,356 --> 01:17:12,256
preparing meals here.

783
01:17:12,325 --> 01:17:13,758
I was the cook.

784
01:17:13,826 --> 01:17:16,761
Jason should've been watched!

785
01:17:16,829 --> 01:17:17,761
Every minute!

786
01:17:17,830 --> 01:17:19,195
He was-

787
01:17:22,268 --> 01:17:24,702
He wasn't
a very good swimmer.

788
01:17:27,273 --> 01:17:29,707
We can go now... dear.

789
01:17:29,776 --> 01:17:32,711
I think we should wait
for Mr. Christy.

790
01:17:32,779 --> 01:17:35,213
Oh, that's not necessary.

791
01:17:35,281 --> 01:17:37,806
I don't understand.

792
01:17:38,885 --> 01:17:40,716
Help me!

793
01:17:40,787 --> 01:17:41,719
Help!

794
01:17:41,788 --> 01:17:43,722
Help, Mommy!

795
01:17:43,790 --> 01:17:44,722
Help!

796
01:17:44,791 --> 01:17:46,725
Help, Mommy!

797
01:17:46,793 --> 01:17:47,725
Mommy, help!

798
01:17:47,794 --> 01:17:49,728
I am, Jason.

799
01:17:49,796 --> 01:17:51,730
I am.

800
01:17:51,798 --> 01:17:52,730
Help!

801
01:17:52,799 --> 01:17:54,232
Oh, God.

802
01:17:54,300 --> 01:17:57,235
You see, Jason was my son,

803
01:17:57,303 --> 01:17:59,362
and today is his birthday.

804
01:17:59,439 --> 01:18:02,237
Where's Mr. Christy?

805
01:18:02,308 --> 01:18:06,244
Oh, I couldn't let them
open this place again.

806
01:18:06,312 --> 01:18:07,244
Could I?

807
01:18:08,815 --> 01:18:10,749
Not after what happened.

808
01:18:14,487 --> 01:18:18,253
Oh, my sweet, innocent Jason.

809
01:18:19,258 --> 01:18:21,692
My only child...

810
01:18:21,761 --> 01:18:23,194
Jason.

811
01:18:28,267 --> 01:18:29,700
You let him drown.

812
01:18:29,769 --> 01:18:31,964
You never paid any attention.

813
01:18:33,272 --> 01:18:36,207
Look at what you did to him.

814
01:18:36,275 --> 01:18:40,575
Look what you did to him!

815
01:18:42,081 --> 01:18:43,309
Aah!

816
01:18:54,794 --> 01:18:55,726
Ohh...

817
01:19:02,301 --> 01:19:05,293
Aah! Aah!

818
01:19:05,371 --> 01:19:06,963
Aah!

819
01:19:15,314 --> 01:19:21,112
Aah!

820
01:19:42,308 --> 01:19:43,775
Kill her, Mommy.

821
01:19:43,843 --> 01:19:45,538
Kill her!

822
01:19:48,848 --> 01:19:51,339
Don't let her get away, Mommy.

823
01:19:51,417 --> 01:19:53,282
Don't let her live.

824
01:19:53,352 --> 01:19:55,786
I won't, Jason.

825
01:19:55,855 --> 01:19:57,288
I won't.

826
01:21:05,358 --> 01:21:06,655
Come, dear.

827
01:21:06,726 --> 01:21:10,787
It'll be easier for you
than it was for Jason.

828
01:21:14,367 --> 01:21:16,801
Kill her, Mommy.

829
01:21:16,869 --> 01:21:18,063
Kill her.

830
01:21:19,805 --> 01:21:20,965
Kill her.

831
01:21:21,040 --> 01:21:22,371
Ahhh!

832
01:21:54,974 --> 01:21:56,100
Uhhh!

833
01:22:57,837 --> 01:22:59,771
Kill her, Mommy.

834
01:22:59,839 --> 01:23:01,272
Kill her.

835
01:23:01,340 --> 01:23:02,773
She can't hide.

836
01:23:02,842 --> 01:23:04,776
No place to hide.

837
01:23:04,844 --> 01:23:06,778
Get her, Mommy.

838
01:23:06,846 --> 01:23:08,279
Get her.

839
01:23:08,347 --> 01:23:16,286
Kill her.

840
01:25:46,805 --> 01:25:47,931
Aah!

841
01:27:33,278 --> 01:27:34,711
Aah!

842
01:27:42,287 --> 01:27:43,219
No!

843
01:27:43,288 --> 01:27:44,220
Aah!

844
01:27:48,293 --> 01:27:49,726
Aah!

845
01:30:27,986 --> 01:30:29,248
Aah!

846
01:30:42,233 --> 01:30:45,168
No!

847
01:30:45,236 --> 01:30:46,669
3 milligrams of Valium.

848
01:30:46,738 --> 01:30:48,171
It's all right now.

849
01:30:48,239 --> 01:30:49,171
It's over.

850
01:30:49,240 --> 01:30:50,172
Everything's over.

851
01:30:53,745 --> 01:30:54,677
Roll over.

852
01:31:06,758 --> 01:31:07,690
O.K.

853
01:31:15,767 --> 01:31:18,634
Your folks are on the way up.

854
01:31:21,206 --> 01:31:23,140
Is anyone else alive?

855
01:31:25,210 --> 01:31:27,178
Are they all dead?

856
01:31:27,245 --> 01:31:29,145
Yes, ma'am.

857
01:31:29,214 --> 01:31:32,650
Two of my men pulled you
out of the lake.

858
01:31:32,717 --> 01:31:35,151
We thought you were dead, too.

859
01:31:35,220 --> 01:31:38,656
Do you remember very much?

860
01:31:38,723 --> 01:31:40,156
The boy.

861
01:31:40,225 --> 01:31:42,159
Is he dead, too?

862
01:31:42,227 --> 01:31:43,159
Who?

863
01:31:43,228 --> 01:31:44,160
The boy.

864
01:31:44,229 --> 01:31:45,161
Jason.

865
01:31:47,232 --> 01:31:48,164
Jason?

866
01:31:48,233 --> 01:31:51,168
In the lake.
The one who attacked me.

867
01:31:51,236 --> 01:31:53,830
The one who pulled me
underneath the water.

868
01:31:55,240 --> 01:31:59,267
Ma'am, we didn't find any boy.

869
01:32:01,246 --> 01:32:02,178
But he...

870
01:32:07,986 --> 01:32:10,682
Then he's still there.
